# Grilled Mexican Street Corn

> Elote - the classic Mexican street food of corn on the cob charred on the grill, then slathered in a spicy and creamy chili-, garlic-, and Cotija cheeseâ€“spiked sauce. #vegetable #side #mexican #grill

Set grill to high heat.

- Mayonnaise | 1/4 cup | 
- Sour Cream | 1/4 cup | 
- Cotija Cheese | 1/2 cup, more for serving | Finely crumbled
- Chili Powder | Ancho, 1/2 tsp | 
- Garlic | 1 clove | Minced
- Cilantro | 1/4 cup | Chopped

Combine ingredients for sauce.

- Corn | 4 ears | Shucked

When grill is hot, place corn directly over hot side of grill and cook, rotating occasionally, until cooked through and charred in spots on all sides, about 8 minutes total.

- Lime | 1 cut | Cut into wedges

To assemble, spread sauce over entire ear of corn, sprinkle on additional cheese, and squeeze lime.
